							A hostile environment, I know it when I see it.  When someone is banned for a week then banned for another week for homophobic phrases and then returns and makes yet another post about gays and pedophiles, when that person has a very, very lousy history of linking gays and pedophiles, that person is purposefully creating an environment that drives posters away.  You simply do not have the built-up goodwill to go down that road.<br />
<br />
If your purpose is to skirt the rules to try to drive posters away you will be banned, using our rule set.  If your purpose is to alter the rule set to prevent posters from being driven away then use the process we have in place to change the rule set.
